        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-10-14T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-10-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="366"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d366">
                <head>366. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in the Philippines</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d366fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 110.12–HO/10–1555. Secret; Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Manila</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-10-15T01:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1955—1 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secun1">Secun</gloss> 41. From <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1"
                        >Hoover</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d366fn2">
                        <p>Under Secretary <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName> and
                                <persName corresp="#p_HJB1">John B. Hollister</persName> were in
                            Manila as part of a tour of several Asian countries. In <gloss
                                target="#t_Secun1">Secun</gloss> 39, October 13, <persName
                                corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName> commented on the subject of
                            additional U.S. aid to the Philippines:</p>
                        <p>“It appears clear we have problem in supporting Philippines and keeping
                            them in stable financial position. Huge figures which have been bandied
                            about in past on subject of additional aid are obviously unrealistic and
                            I have emphasized that congressional program framework leaves us with
                            very little flexibility. However, I am hopeful that with some
                            adjustments in 1956 program planning it will be possible to give some
                            additional aid.” (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> 110.12–HO/10–1355)
                            Additional information on the <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1"
                                >Hoover</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_HJB1">Hollister</persName>
                            trip is <hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> 110.12–HO and <hi rend="italic"
                                >Ibid.,</hi> Conference Files: Lot 59 D 95, <gloss target="#t_CF1"
                                >CF</gloss> 534–<gloss target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 541.</p>
                    </note> After thorough review of Phil aid program, <persName corresp="#p_HJB1"
                        >Hollister</persName> and I are agreed that $4.2 million should be added to
                    rural development program here and that this decision should be announced as
                    soon as possible in order to achieve maximum impact on Phil elections Nov 8.</p>
                <p>As to source of funds, every effort will be made by <gloss target="#t_ICA1"
                        >ICA</gloss> Mission here to transfer various amounts from other projects
                    but we are agreed program is fairly tight and most of money will have to come
                    from elsewhere—either President’s emergency fund or reserves. I shall discuss
                    this aspect of matter further upon return Washington.</p>
                <pb facs="0642" n="614" xml:id="pg_614"/>
                <p>Meanwhile Ambassador will explore with <persName corresp="#p_MR1"
                        >Magsaysay</persName> question of best method of making and timing
                    announcement and will recommend to Department. Our present thinking is that
                    announcement should be made in Manila by Ambassador to achieve maximum
                    effectiveness here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FH1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Ferguson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
